Candle craft for school
One day Sally's class had show and tell.
Her best friend showed a picture that she had painted.
She told the class how she made the picture and everybody liked it.
Then Sally decided she wanted to make something special for show and tell.
So Sally went to the library and check out a book.
Sally read that candles could be made by melting crayons and pouring them into a cup.
Finally she decided she wanted to make a red candle.
Sally found some crayons and a cup at home.
She put the crayons into the cup.
She melted the wax in the cup and held a string that made a wick.
The wax hardened quickly.
At last the beautiful candle was finished.
She put her new candle in a holder and began decorating with ribbons.
The next day Sally carried the candle to the school.
When she arrived she asked her teacher if she could be in show and tell.
She won the show and tell grand prize for her candle.
Her friend was happy for her and they celebrated after school.
Living underground the life of a mole
The mole is a small furry animal that lives underground.
It moves around in tunnels that it digs.
The moles has changed its life in four ways because it lives underground.
First the mole has short solid legs that are good for digging tunnels.
This helps the mole dig tunnels so it can hunt for worms to eat.
The mole also digs a home tunnel where it sleeps.
Second good hearing is important so the mole can tell when other animals are in its tunnels.
The mole's ears are tiny because larger ears would get in the way when digging.
Third the mole's eyes are very small and they can only see light and dark.
This is because the mole live underground where it's dark so it's not important for them to see.
Finally because it is dark underground the mole has a special way of figuring out where it's going.
Going forward the mole feels its way with its nose and hair on the front feet.
When the mole is going backward it's tail tells it which way to go.
